@*
    Services hub. Presents all three services together, then routes into each. The pattern
    borrowed (structure only, not copy) from an agency Scott worked at: lead each service with
    a pain-point question that names the reader's problem before pitching. The question is about
    the reader, so it makes no claim about Scott and is safe to write freely.

    Order is deliberate: nopCommerce first (sharpest Upwork wedge, best proof), .NET second
    (strongest backed claim, widest market), websites last (least backed). Copy is placeholder.
*@

<section class="section--lede">
    <div class="container">
        <p class="topper">Services</p>
        <h1 class="header">What I can help with</h1>
        <p class="text lede__text">
            Three ways I work with businesses and organizations. All of it is real development,
            on live systems, by someone who's done this inside agencies for years.
        </p>
        <a class="button button--lg" asp-controller="Contact" asp-action="Index">Schedule a consultation</a>
    </div>
</section>

<section>
    <div class="container">
        <ul class="services">
            <li class="service">
                <h2 class="service__title">nopCommerce development</h2>
                <p class="service__hook">Running a nopCommerce store that needs ongoing help?</p>
                <p class="service__text">
                    Custom plugins, integrations, upgrades and fixes on existing stores. Agency
                    experience, working with you directly.
                </p>
                <a class="service__link" asp-controller="Services" asp-action="NopCommerce">
                    nopCommerce development
                </a>
            </li>

            <li class="service">
                <h2 class="service__title">.NET application development</h2>
                <p class="service__hook">Got a .NET application nobody's looking after?</p>
                <p class="service__text">
                    Maintenance, fixes, new features and integrations on existing .NET systems,
                    plus new builds. The back end, not just the front. 25 years of it.
                </p>
                <a class="service__link" asp-controller="Services" asp-action="DotNet">
                    .NET application development
                </a>
            </li>

            <li class="service">
                <h2 class="service__title">Small business websites</h2>
                <p class="service__hook">Need a site people can actually find?</p>
                <p class="service__text">
                    A fast, clean website built to be read by search engines, for businesses on
                    the Colorado Front Range.
                </p>
                <a class="service__link" asp-controller="Services" asp-action="SmallBusiness">
                    Small business websites
                </a>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>

<partial name="_CallToAction" model="@("Not sure which fits? Let's talk it through.")" />
